WEBVTT



00:00:00.768 --> 00:00:10.624
Well hello friends and thank you for joining me in our daily reading from God's Holy Word. Today we're reading Mark chapter 10 verses 13 to 31.

00:00:10.496 --> 00:00:17.984
Now in this lesson Jesus teaches us how to enjoy the blessing of belonging to the kingdom of heaven.

00:00:18.144 --> 00:00:20.032
Before we read, let's pray.

00:00:20.160 --> 00:00:26.848
our Father in heaven, speak to our hearts and help us to hear Jesus. In his name I pray.

00:00:26.976 --> 00:00:28.192
Amen.

00:00:28.512 --> 00:00:31.776
Mark chapter 10 verse 13

00:00:31.456 --> 00:00:35.648
And they were bringing children to him that he might touch them.

00:00:35.360 --> 00:00:37.760
And the disciples rebuked them.

00:00:37.632 --> 00:00:44.288
But when Jesus saw it, he was indignant and said to them, Let the children come to me.

00:00:44.288 --> 00:00:46.016
Do not hinder them.

00:00:45.888 --> 00:00:49.056
For to such belongs the kingdom of God.

00:00:49.280 --> 00:00:55.584
Truly, I say to you, whoever does not receive the kingdom of God like a child,

00:00:55.520 --> 00:00:57.184
Shall not enter it.

00:00:57.440 --> 00:01:00.256
And he took them in his arms and blessed them.

00:01:00.096 --> 00:01:02.656
Laying his hands on them.

00:01:03.232 --> 00:01:12.096
and as he was setting out on his journey a man ran up and knelt before him and asked him good teacher what must i do

00:01:11.904 --> 00:01:13.856
To inherit eternal life.

00:01:13.952 --> 00:01:15.776
And Jesus said to him,

00:01:15.552 --> 00:01:20.256
Why do you call me good? No one is good except God alone.

00:01:20.480 --> 00:01:22.336
You know the commandments.

00:01:22.240 --> 00:01:26.208
Do not murder. Do not commit adultery. Do not steal.

00:01:26.080 --> 00:01:31.040
Do not bear false witness. Do not defraud. Honor your father and mother.

00:01:31.648 --> 00:01:37.728
And he said to him, Teacher, all these I have kept from my youth.

00:01:38.240 --> 00:01:40.864
And Jesus looking at him,

00:01:40.928 --> 00:01:42.240
loved him.

00:01:42.304 --> 00:01:45.856
And said to him, You laugh one thing,

00:01:45.856 --> 00:01:46.976
Go

00:01:46.784 --> 00:01:50.048
Sell all that you have and give to the poor.

00:01:50.016 --> 00:01:52.448
And you will have treasure in heaven.

00:01:52.384 --> 00:01:53.568
And come.

00:01:53.536 --> 00:01:54.752
Follow me.

00:01:55.584 --> 00:01:58.080
Disheartened by the saying,

00:01:58.016 --> 00:02:00.096
He went away sorrowful,

00:02:00.032 --> 00:02:02.464
For he had great possessions.

00:02:02.752 --> 00:02:11.136
And Jesus looked around and said to his disciples, how difficult it will be for those who have wealth to enter the kingdom of God.

00:02:11.584 --> 00:02:14.720
And the disciples were amazed at his words.

00:02:14.656 --> 00:02:24.704
But Jesus said to them again, children, how difficult it is to enter the kingdom of God. It is easier for a camel to go through the.

00:02:24.224 --> 00:02:25.888
Through the eye of a needle.

00:02:25.856 --> 00:02:29.024
Than for a rich person to enter the kingdom of God.

00:02:29.408 --> 00:02:33.280
And they were exceedingly astonished, and said to him.

00:02:33.408 --> 00:02:35.360
Then who can be saved?

00:02:35.776 --> 00:02:38.016
Jesus looked at them and said,

00:02:37.888 --> 00:02:39.328
With man,

00:02:39.104 --> 00:02:40.832
It is impossible.

00:02:40.704 --> 00:02:42.208
But not with God.

00:02:42.144 --> 00:02:44.352
For all things are possible.

00:02:44.160 --> 00:02:45.472
With God.

00:02:46.368 --> 00:02:48.256
Peter began to say to him,

00:02:48.096 --> 00:02:51.616
See, we have left everything and followed you.

00:02:51.904 --> 00:02:53.376
Jesus said,

00:02:53.280 --> 00:03:02.560
Truly, I say to you, there is no one who has left house or brothers or sisters or mother or father or children or lands.

00:03:02.368 --> 00:03:05.280
For my sake and for the gospel.

00:03:05.312 --> 00:03:15.360
Who will not receive a hundredfold now in this time, houses and brothers and sisters and mothers and children and lands with?

00:03:14.880 --> 00:03:15.680
With

00:03:15.488 --> 00:03:17.088
Persecutions,

00:03:17.216 --> 00:03:19.136
And then the age to come,

00:03:18.944 --> 00:03:20.480
Eternal life

00:03:20.640 --> 00:03:23.200
But many who are first.

00:03:22.976 --> 00:03:24.512
will be last.

00:03:24.416 --> 00:03:25.792
And the last,

00:03:25.984 --> 00:03:27.168
First.

00:03:28.448 --> 00:03:31.200
In his teaching on the kingdom of heaven,

00:03:31.200 --> 00:03:34.176
Jesus cradles children.

00:03:33.984 --> 00:03:36.064
Confronts a rich man.

00:03:35.776 --> 00:03:38.112
And comforts his disciples.

00:03:38.080 --> 00:03:38.976
First,

00:03:38.784 --> 00:03:40.736
The children, parents,

00:03:40.448 --> 00:03:42.528
Who believed in Jesus, who

00:03:42.240 --> 00:03:52.288
Brought their children to Jesus to be blessed by him, as all faithful Christian parents do. we bring them to his church, and we ask Jesus.

00:03:51.808 --> 00:03:56.704
Ask Jesus to save them and protect them and keep them for himself. Amen.

00:03:57.248 --> 00:04:07.296
His disciples, however, took the attitude that Jesus was too busy for infants. His kingdom ministry was too important for him to be bothered by parents of children.

00:04:06.816 --> 00:04:10.720
of children, and Jesus got hot with anger.

00:04:10.688 --> 00:04:12.832
For hindering them.

00:04:12.864 --> 00:04:15.840
For his kingdom belongs to.

00:04:15.616 --> 00:04:20.448
Infants and toddlers, the little ones you can take up in your arms.

00:04:20.096 --> 00:04:21.824
He says,, in fact,,

00:04:21.568 --> 00:04:25.600
Whoever does not receive the kingdom of God like a child,

00:04:25.440 --> 00:04:27.104
Shall not enter it.

00:04:27.584 --> 00:04:31.392
Little children aren't people who do

00:04:31.296 --> 00:04:33.600
But people who are done for,

00:04:33.728 --> 00:04:37.280
They don't provide for themselves, they are provided for.

00:04:37.024 --> 00:04:40.960
They don't work to earn, they simply receive what is given.

00:04:40.800 --> 00:04:42.112
So it is.

00:04:42.080 --> 00:04:44.992
That by grace we are saved.

00:04:44.736 --> 00:04:52.800
Through faith. and this is not our own doing. it is the gift of God, not a result of works, so that no one can boast.

00:04:54.272 --> 00:04:59.040
Notice how the rich man didn't understand this. He asks,

00:04:58.784 --> 00:05:00.960
What must I do?

00:05:00.832 --> 00:05:10.880
To inherit eternal life. here that I've seen, surely there's something I must accomplish, some way I can work myself into it. So Jesus, in an often misunderstood.

00:05:10.400 --> 00:05:16.960
This understood passage points him to God's commands. Don't murder, don't steal, honor your parents, etc.

00:05:16.736 --> 00:05:19.616
But not because Jesus is saying,

00:05:19.296 --> 00:05:23.136
you can save yourself by your obedience to God

00:05:23.552 --> 00:05:33.600
But in order to humble the man to show him he is unworthy of the kingdom, that he hasn't loved God with all his heart, soul, strength and mind, nor has he loved.

00:05:33.120 --> 00:05:36.992
He loved his neighbor as himself, which is the whole point of the commandments.

00:05:36.928 --> 00:05:43.840
But the guy is so proud of himself, he hasn't begun to see all the ways he breaks God's law of love.

00:05:43.616 --> 00:05:49.728
in word and deed and desire so Jesus presses him you said

00:05:49.504 --> 00:05:51.104
I'm a good teacher.

00:05:51.168 --> 00:05:54.336
But you know that only God is good, right?

00:05:54.656 --> 00:06:00.352
And if that's the case, how can you stand here and tell me you yourself are a good man?

00:06:00.032 --> 00:06:08.256
don't you know yourself? don't you know you love yourself more than god or others? that's not good!

00:06:08.544 --> 00:06:17.088
Here's how I'll prove it to you, and more importantly, here's how I'll cut you off with the knees and humble you. so he says you lack one thing.

00:06:17.024 --> 00:06:17.920
Go!

00:06:18.144 --> 00:06:19.808
Sell all that you have.

00:06:19.616 --> 00:06:21.280
And give to the poor.

00:06:20.992 --> 00:06:22.944
And you will have treasure in heaven.

00:06:22.752 --> 00:06:23.904
And come.

00:06:23.936 --> 00:06:25.216
Follow me.

00:06:25.760 --> 00:06:27.296
And the man didn't.

00:06:27.392 --> 00:06:32.128
Because he really loved his possessions more than the good God.

00:06:31.872 --> 00:06:34.048
Standing right in front of him.

00:06:34.336 --> 00:06:36.224
And he went away sorrowful.

00:06:36.864 --> 00:06:39.296
Now Jesus wasn't being mean.

00:06:40.512 --> 00:06:46.368
And he certainly wasn't saying you can buy heaven by selling your possessions and giving to the poor.

00:06:46.784 --> 00:06:49.312
But Jesus was being truthful and loving.

00:06:49.408 --> 00:06:53.696
Jesus wasn't teaching him if you just jump through one more hoop you're in.

00:06:53.728 --> 00:07:01.152
He used the law like a mirror to show the man his own wicked heart, but the man didn't have eyes to see.

00:07:01.632 --> 00:07:05.888
Look, you'll never do enough if eternal life is something you can get.

00:07:05.760 --> 00:07:07.232
By doing

00:07:07.744 --> 00:07:10.496
But how proud the man who thinks he can.

00:07:10.720 --> 00:07:12.896
You've got to receive it.

00:07:12.608 --> 00:07:14.368
As a free gift.

00:07:14.752 --> 00:07:18.624
As Paul in Romans says, now to the one who works.

00:07:18.720 --> 00:07:23.072
His wages are not counted as a gift, but as his due.

00:07:23.424 --> 00:07:26.144
And to the one who does not work,

00:07:25.952 --> 00:07:30.080
But believes in him who justifies the ungodly.

00:07:30.048 --> 00:07:32.768
His faith is counted as righteousness.

00:07:33.504 --> 00:07:42.272
How blessed then is the man or the woman, the boy or the girl whom the Lord forgives and counts as righteous as a gift.

00:07:42.080 --> 00:07:43.776
Through faith in Jesus.

00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:48.160
Now, in the final encounter, Jesus comforts his disciples.

00:07:48.128 --> 00:07:54.368
well, first he disturbs them. he says it's impossible for rich people to get themselves into god's kingdom.

00:07:54.912 --> 00:08:00.544
It would be easier for a camel to pass through the eye of a beetle. it can't be done, not by them.

00:08:00.544 --> 00:08:02.496
Riches won't help you get in.

00:08:02.592 --> 00:08:05.504
But they can be a hindrance to getting in.

00:08:05.408 --> 00:08:09.248
rich people who put their hopes in their own kingdoms in this world.

00:08:09.088 --> 00:08:12.064
will be disinterested in the kingdom of God.

00:08:12.992 --> 00:08:14.880
So who then can be saved?

00:08:15.008 --> 00:08:17.760
Jesus says with man it is impossible.

00:08:17.792 --> 00:08:19.392
But not with God,

00:08:19.232 --> 00:08:21.728
For all things are possible with God,

00:08:21.824 --> 00:08:24.608
God can humble the proud

00:08:24.448 --> 00:08:26.464
and give grace to the humble.

00:08:26.624 --> 00:08:29.472
After all, God saved Abraham.

00:08:29.280 --> 00:08:30.656
And Job,

00:08:30.432 --> 00:08:32.064
Anzacchius.

00:08:32.064 --> 00:08:33.664
All rich men.

00:08:33.472 --> 00:08:34.880
Whom he humbled.

00:08:35.776 --> 00:08:43.136
then peter thinking of the rich man begins to say you know we've given everything to follow you and jesus.

00:08:42.816 --> 00:08:45.856
Not rebuking him.

00:08:45.888 --> 00:08:47.616
Cuts him off.

00:08:47.648 --> 00:08:49.184
And comforts him.

00:08:49.152 --> 00:08:53.312
He knows he's giving Peter the kingdom. Peter isn't going to earn it.

00:08:53.664 --> 00:08:59.200
But the disciples of Jesus do give up a lot as they follow Jesus.

00:08:59.008 --> 00:09:00.800
Jesus wants

00:09:00.576 --> 00:09:10.624
To comfort us, he says, you can't out-give your father in heaven. Truly, I say to you, there is no one who has left house or brothers or sisters or mother or father or children.

00:09:10.144 --> 00:09:11.904
Or children or lands?

00:09:12.032 --> 00:09:13.440
For my sake,

00:09:13.344 --> 00:09:14.816
And for the gospel.

00:09:14.816 --> 00:09:16.544
Who will not receive,

00:09:16.384 --> 00:09:18.880
A hundredfold now in this time.

00:09:18.752 --> 00:09:22.784
Houses and brothers and sisters and mothers and children and lands.

00:09:22.784 --> 00:09:24.576
With persecutions,

00:09:24.864 --> 00:09:26.944
And in the age to come.

00:09:27.040 --> 00:09:28.640
Eternal life.

00:09:29.152 --> 00:09:32.608
what a generous father we serve

00:09:32.416 --> 00:09:39.232
He gives salvation freely to those who look away from themselves and to his son.

00:09:39.328 --> 00:09:43.104
And any loss we might suffer in serving him.

00:09:43.008 --> 00:09:45.664
Is more than made up for

00:09:45.664 --> 00:09:46.752
By him.

00:09:48.512 --> 00:09:49.888
It's worth it.

00:09:50.016 --> 00:09:51.648
To follow Jesus.

00:09:51.872 --> 00:09:53.088
Let's pray.

00:09:53.280 --> 00:09:58.016
Father in heaven have mercy on us forgive our sins

00:09:58.272 --> 00:10:00.480
Grant us to be righteous,

00:10:00.288 --> 00:10:01.728
In Christ.

00:10:01.664 --> 00:10:04.960
And take us for your children into your heavenly kingdom.

00:10:04.800 --> 00:10:06.528
In his name I pray.

00:10:06.656 --> 00:10:07.904
Amen.

00:10:08.352 --> 00:10:12.064
Amen. Well, thank you for listening in, and I hope you'll join me next time.
